commitResults.messageTitle: Improve code quality of Find.java by breaking main method into smaller methods and better following SLAP and SRP principles
Include asserts in Find.java and update its Find.java tests
Update DayPlan.java to make methods shorter and adhere better to code quality standard
Refactor Storage.java to split up large main function into smaller functions better suited for code quality standard
Refactor Find command to use streams for keyword matching
commitResults.messageBody:
The Find command previously used nested loops to match tasks against user-provided keywords. This resulted in imperative-style code with reduced readability.

The code is now refactored to use Java Streams for better readability and conciseness. Streams simplify the checking of whether any keyword is present in a taskâ€™s name.

Using streams improves the clarity of the matching logic by expressing it declaratively, making the intent clearer.

commitResults.messageTitle: Merge pull request #1 from teesha902/branch-A-Streams
Add HelpCommand to display available commands and formats
commitResults.messageBody:
The PiggyPlanner application currently lacks an in-built guide to inform users of available commands and their respective formats. This can cause frustration for new users unfamiliar with the input structure.

To improve user experience, a HelpCommand has been added. When the user enters the "help" command, the program displays a comprehensive list of commands with their expected formats. This allows users to quickly learn how to interact with the PiggyPlanner.
